'''Otr''' was a [[demon]] "in otter's form" who appears briefly in ''[[The Legend of Sigurd and Gudrún]]''.<ref name="history">{{SG|I}}</ref>

==History==
Otr was the son of [[Hreidmar]], a [[demon]], and the brother of [[Fáfnir]] and [[Regin]]. He thought [[silver]] [[salmon]] were sweet to eat. One day, when he was fishing at the "black waters" of [[Andvari]]'s falls, he was killed with a stone by [[Loki]] before being stripped and flayed. Loki and the other gods later brought Otr's body to Hreidmar’s halls to trade for housing.<ref name="history"/>

